ork in manageable segments lets teams continually test, validate, and troubleshoot issues during development, thus allowing risks to be identified and dealt with as they arise. For BookMaster, which has multiple user roles and processes, this approach is the best way to reduce integration risks.                                     4) Flexibility: BookMaster could place priority on performing core functionalities at first, but with flexibility to tweak the next phases according to user preferences. This strategy is fully aligned with the project growth and is modeled to make changes as the users become more expert in handling this system.                                                    5) Incremental Delivery Similar to Business Systems: Like other systems for the purpose of business, BookMaster can take a phased approach by launching critical features early (for example, booking systems, orders) and expanding the inventory reports late. Each stream, whether continuous or incremental, adds functional value to the users' experience, moving them gradually towards the improved system.2.      Identify and analyze ethical concerns for the case study and make reasoned ethical choices. (10 marksŁ©1) Privacy and Data Security(Confidentiality) : Developers should implement strong data protection mechanisms and adhere to strict regulations to prevent data breaches or unauthorized access to customer information. 2) Competence: Engineers must have sufficient skills to ensure that the system processes data efficiently. Lack of adequate programming capabilities can lead to design flaws that can disrupt order processing or data processing, leading to user dissatisfaction.3) Intellectual Property and Ownership : Books are the intellectual property of authors and publishers. The system must respect copyright. Selling or lending unauthorized books can lead to serious legal and financial consequences.4) Inclusivity and Accessibility: Systems should be designed to be used by people from diverse backgrounds, using common design principles to ensure that special groups can use them effectively and prevent legal penalties and damage to the organization's reputation.5) Transparency and Accountability : Developers must comply with the licensing terms of these open-source tools if uses open-source software. Unauthorized modification or use would be unethical and potentially illegal.6) Environmental Impact : Improper handling and overuse of information systems and their infrastructure have an impact on the environment, and responsible e-waste management and recycling programs are implemented to promote sustainability. 3.      What are the non-functional requirements that might impact the system, and how might they do so?  (10 marks)1)Security requirement: The web browser could be accessed by all the customers. HoweverŁ¬the GUI used by the warehouse staff could not be accessed be anyone else. The interface used to define the books for sale, manage out of print and obtain financial reports could only be accessed by the manager. 2)Usability requirement: The GUI designed for the warehouse staff is supposed to be brief, clear and organized which enables them to address the orders more efficiently. The manipulation of changing the record of stock on hand should be easily accomplished. The interface used by the manage should be easy-to-use. Information including the time of the orders and the remaining number of stocks should be easy to acquire and clearly presented. The interface accessed by the customers should be provide the information of the book comprehensively including the author, the published year and so on.3)Efficiency requirement: The record of the historical orders should be updated timely. The remaining stock of various kinds of books should be updated timely. 4)Dependability requirement: the monthly generated sales report should be reliable. The information within should be precise and accountable. The information of the orders should be precisely recorded and not easily lost. 5)Scalability requirement: when the orders grow extremely large, the system is supposed to be able to handle the increase load without degrading performance. The database is supposed to record the data accurately and access the data required effectively with increased load. 6)Safety requirement: The safety of the data privacy should be guaranteed. The private data including the payment information, addressŁ¬phone numbers and so on is not supposed to be leaked out.4.      What challenges might arise when working in collaboration, and what do you propose to overcome these challenges? (10 marks)The difference in communication styles among team members can lead to misunderstandings and miscommunication, especially when using online communication methods like email, which lack tone and body language. In this case, it is important to encourage team members to hold face-to-face meetings to ensure clear communication. Attendees should actively express their ideas and listen attentively to others' perspectives. When online communication is necessary, pay attention to the way of expression to avoid offending other members and ensure that the information is conveyed correctly.The members may have different working styles, which can also delay accomplishing tasks. Some individuals prefer detailed planning, while others may prefer a more flexible approach. These different styles can cause project delays and even lead to conflicts among members. To solve this problem, it is necessary to clarify the responsibilities of each team member and the goals of the project at the beginning of the project and determine tasks and deadlines. Using project management tools can also help manage processes and ensure that all members can see the progress of the project. In addition, it is necessary to regularly review and update the responsibilities and task assignments of members to adapt to changes in the project.When working remotely, workers sometimes fail to see the real-time synchronization of work progress, which consequently can lead to the suspicion of team members and result in the breakdown of trust and working atmosphere. Therefore, creating a work environment that makes people feel respected and inclusive is necessary. In this environment, everyone can express their opinions and concerns, which helps reduce disputes. Transparency in project progress and fair arrangements also contribute to building trust within the team.5.      What measures can BookMaster take to ensure that the warehouse interface is user-friendly for employees of all backgrounds, including those with different levels of technical proficiency? (10 marks)1) Intuitive Design: The interface should use obvious pictograms, plain language, and step-by-step workflow, which can accommodate users with all sorts of technical degrees. 2) Multilingual Support: The fact that employees could be very different from each other can only imply introducing the interface in multiple languages to allow non-native speakers. 3) Minimalist Layout: Ensure that the interface is not filled with too many pieces of information, which will lead to confusion. Only the functions that are essential and the details that are critical for the user should be highlighted, in order to reduce the cognitive overload. 4) Training and Tutorials: Integrate internal tutors or step-by-step guides aimed at new users, supplemented by detailed sections where workers can look for help on the system. 5) Accessibility Features: Enable features for users' accessibility, e.g. high-contrast mode, bigger font, and keyboard navigation for people with visual or physical disability. 6) Error Handling and Feedback: Show distinct error messages, combined with instant reactions after activities, which serve the purpose of assisting users to realize where they have gone wrong and how they can rectify such mistakes. 7) Role-Specific Customization: Adapt the UI to the roles of different users. Warehouse workers should be presented with the very core of the system that includes packed items and the stock, while the managers certainly need some additional reporting features. 8) Mobile-Friendly Interface: Test the system for availability on various devices, including hand scanners or smartphones, which are the most widely used devices in warehouses. 9) Consistent Layout: Use the same position for the buttons and menu items on all pages to make it easier to master the interface. 10) User Testing and Feedback: The process of obtaining feedback should be continuous, both from the warehouse employees and usability tests, which identities which improvements have an impact, this will be a continuous measure.Section 5. Peer review form templateCPT203 Coursework  Peer review Individual Contribution for Group Report Group Number: <x>NameID NumberContribution (%)Please enter an integer, for example 15% contribution, please enter 15. The sum of this column should be 100Signature1.  Zihang Wu225408820Îâ×ÎşĽ2. Shuyuan Zhang225301720ŐĹĘéÔ´3. Hengqi Liang225481420Áşşăçů4. Zhouzhi Li225411820Ŕî×żÖ®5. Yijia Chen225319120łÂôŕŮ¤END10